GcompBART: G-computation using Bayesian Additive Regression Trees
Overview
GcompBART extends https://cran.r-project.org/package=SoftBart for G-computation with time-varying components. It supports flexible Bayesian regression with longitudinal priors and additional hyperparameters for complex data structures.
Features

Wraps SoftBart for base functionality.
Adds time-varying extensions: alpha_vec, eta, phi.

Supports grouped predictors via tgroup.
High-performance implementation using Rcpp.
Installation
From CRAN (once published):
install.packages("GcompBART")



From GitHub (development version):
# install.packages("devtools")
devtools::install_github("yourusername/GcompBART")



Quick Start
library(GcompBART)



Example data
X <- matrix(rnorm(100), nrow = 20) Y <- rnorm(20)
Build options
opts <- Opts(num_burn = 1000, update_tvp = TRUE)
Build hypers
hypers <- Hypers(X, Y, tgroup = c(0, 1, 1, 2), alpha_vec = 0.5)
Fit model (example placeholder)
fit <- BMfits(X, Y, opts = opts, hypers = hypers)



Documentation

See ?Opts and ?Hypers for details.
Vignette: vignette("intro-to-GcompBART")
